io.sphere.sdk.client

Interface SphereClientFactory


  • public interface SphereClientFactory
    A factory to instantiate platform Java clients which use CompletionStage as future implementation. 
    import io.sphere.sdk.client.SphereClient;
import io.sphere.sdk.client.SphereClientFactory;

    public class JavaClientInstantiationExample {
    public void instantiate() {
        final SphereClientFactory factory = SphereClientFactory.of();
        final SphereClient client = factory.createClient(
                "jvm-sdk-dev-1", //replace with your project key
                "ELqF0rykXD2fyS8s-IhIPKfQ", //replace with your client id
                "222222222222222222222222222222226"); //replace with your client secret
    }
}

    See the test code.

      • createClientOfApiConfigAndAccessToken

        default SphereClient createClientOfApiConfigAndAccessToken(SphereApiConfig config,
                                                           String accessToken,
                                                           HttpClient httpClient)
        Creates a client which relies on an access token and does not refresh it, it reuses an existing http client. A possible use case is keeping the clientSecret secret and/or instantiate a client which is used for few requests for a limited time. The underlying http client does not get closed by closing the client
        Parameters:
        config - the configuration to use the API
        accessToken - the token belonging to the project in config
        httpClient - the http client used for performing requests
        Returns:
        client
